variables
========
Data types
Number
String
Boolean
Other, Object

Number
-------
one type of number, can be written with or without decimal places
var_1 = 3
var_2 = 24
Scientific notation
-----------------
var x = 12e2 => 1200
var y = 12e-3 => 12/1000

string
------
name = "Manoj Gautam"
last_name = "hello world"

boolean_variable
--------------------
flag = true // remember capital letter
flag = false // remember small letter

typeof
-------
typeof(variable) //can be used to check the type of variable


typecasting in javascript (Conversion from one type to other)
==============================================================
x = 12
parseInt(x) => 12
parseFloat(x) => 12.0
String(x) => "12.0"


